{"root":{"children":[{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"color: #FFD700","text":"Work from School","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"heading","version":1,"tag":"h1"},{"children":[],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1,"textFormat":0},{"children":[{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Last night I had a brief experience of conflict where I chose to “let it go” rather than continue trying to barrage the situation with my reasons why it should change. Reflecting over the situation, I decided that people should aim to release conflict rather than dealing with it head-on because it's better for their health and leads to better resolutions.","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Alain Trautmann writes in his abstract ","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":2,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Mechanisms underlying chronic fatigue…","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"(2021) that chronic activation of the HPA (hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal) axis can lead to chronic fatigue.","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":2},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Susan Fried in her 2023 work ","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":10,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Can’t We Just Get Along?","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":" says, “Essentially, our brains are wired to ","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":2,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"react","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":" to conflict, but not to ","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":2,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"respond","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":" productively.” This means that only through avoiding conflict can we process facts objectively and respond to the ","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":2,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"illusion","type":"text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":" of conflict (living in the minds of others) in a proactive and effective manner.","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":3},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Diplomacy experts will provide various systematic approaches to conflict management (Harvard’s “Program on Negotiation”, “Negotiation Journal”), but these are rooted in the sunk cost fallacy.","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":4},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Releasing conflict is better for individuals for health and resolution.","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":5}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"list","version":1,"listType":"bullet","start":1,"tag":"ul"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":2,"mode":"normal","style":"color: #FFD700","text":"- Jeremiah","type":"text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1,"textFormat":2}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"root","version":1}}